– 2 –
14 Under existing law the Council to Establish Academic Standards for Public
15 Schools is required to establish standards of content and performance for certain
16 courses of study taught in public schools, including courses of study of a foreign or
17 world language. (NRS 389.520) Section 3 of this bill includes American Sign
18 Language as a foreign or world language for which the Council must establish
19 standards of content and performance.
20 Section 4 of this bill requires the Department of Education to conduct a study
21 during the 2025-2026 interim to determine the need for a school for pupils who are
22 deaf or hard of hearing.
